1.40	Section_8_Housing_Choice_Voucher	Section 8 (housing)	Section 8 of the Housing Act of 1937 , often simply known as Section 8, as repeatedly amended, authorizes the payment of rental housing assistance to private landlords on behalf of approximately 3.1 million low-income households. It operates through several programs, the largest of which, the Housing Choice Voucher program, pays a large portion of the rents and utilities of about 2.1 million households. The US Department of Housing and Urban Development manages the Section 8 programs.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/f/f2/Maria_Isabel_Housing_787_Wales_Av_149_St_jeh.jpg/220px-Maria_Isabel_Housing_787_Wales_Av_149_St_jeh.jpg
